The paper proposes a new vector representation for time that can be used in various machine learning architectures to improve their performance. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV).
